Xenomai and RTAI kernel Debian packaging for Linux 3.8.13

This builds Xenomai- and RTAI-patched kernel packages for Debian and
Ubuntu.

RTAI packages are a WIP, and so are disabled by default (see below).

How to build:
=============

# Set up
apt-get install linux-patch-xenomai
wget https://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v3.x/linux-3.8.13.tar.xz \
     -O linux_3.8.13.orig.tar.xz
tar xJf linux_3.8.13.orig.tar.xz --strip-components=1
mkdir linux-rt-deb
cd linux-rt-deb
git clone https://github.com/zultron/kernel-rt-deb2.git debian
debian/rules debian/control; debian/rules orig

# Build binary packages with one of the following:
#   Build everything (probably not what you want)
fakeroot debian/rules binary
#   Build amd64 Xenomai package only
fakeroot make -f debian/rules.gen binary-arch_amd64_xenomai
#   Build i386 vanilla package only, with 16 concurrent threads
fakeroot make MAKE='make -j16' -f debian/rules.gen binary-arch_i386

# Other useful targets:
debian/rules clean
debian/rules maintainerclean

# Create and rebuild source package:
dpkg-source -b .
cd ..
dpkg-source -x *.dsc
cd linux-<version>
dpkg-buildpackage -B

# RTAI packages:
#
# RTAI packages are a WIP, and should be disabled for now.  To build:
# - Uncomment 'rtai.x86' under 'featuresets:' in config/defines and
#   config/{amd64,i386}/defines.
# - Install the RTAI kernel sources:
apt-get install rtai-source

Methodology:
============

Started from a clone of the Debian kernel packaging for Sid, r20131:
git svn clone svn://anonscm.debian.org/svn/kernel/dists/sid/linux/debian

Following Debian Linux Kernel Handbook, 4.3 Building a development
version of the Debian kernel package [4]:

wget https://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v3.x/linux-3.8.13.tar.xz \
     -O linux_3.8.13.orig.tar.xz
tar xJf linux_3.8.13.orig.tar.xz --strip-components=1
mkdir linux-rt-deb
cd linux-rt-deb
git svn clone svn://anonscm.debian.org/svn/kernel/dists/sid/linux/debian

Made changes; see top commits; summary:
- Removed a lot of non-x86 architectures (pkg is x86-only for now)
- Removed the rt feature set
- Imported configs from Ubuntu Raring [3] (Sid configs excluded virtio)
- Added some featureset-friendly tweaks to packaging
- Added the Xenomai feature set
- Added the r8168 driver
- Added the RTAI feature set

